defaultThe defaultActing defaultChairman:default Thank you very much. Do either of you want to make an opening statement or will you just take the questions?
defaultHeather Cousinsdefault: I will just briefly say thank you very much for the opportunity to give evidence on the actions that we have taken in the devolved Administration. I think that in some ways size enables us to trial things and see what works. It is also useful to have in the one department the higher education institutions policy, further education, skills and the employment programme. The fact that that is all in one department means that we can have the co-ordination and collaboration that I think is essential for success. That is all that I wanted to say as an opening remark.
