defaultLord Haskel:default This problem has been around for an awful long time, and a lot of good work has been done on it, as you have just told us. There has also been 
defaulta 
defaultconsiderable amount of evaluation as to the best practice and how to help young employed most effectively. Indeed, 
defaultNorthern Ireland
default has been an effective participant in many transnational programmes, so if so much is known, why is the problem of youth unemployment so intractable? What could we practically do to improve our collective performance? How can we do better?
defaultBrian Smartdefault: You are absolutely right. There is no question about that. In 
defaultNorthern Ireland
default, we have already stated that we have been recipients for many a long period of both peace funding and EU funding. However, with the unprecedented nature of the economic collapse and the banking crisis, the 
defaultRepublic
default of 
defaultIreland
default, our neighbour, gave a guarantee in relation to all banking deposits, which meant that it had to go to the troika to borrow lots of money. We are seeing it from both sides
default: t
defaulthere is not only a general downward trend in economics but particular circumstances in the 
defaultRepublic
